h2 Examples
h3 Base
:example(lang="html") include ./_default.pug

h3 No Border
p.-text Remove all borders by applying the modifier class <code>-no-border</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_borderless.pug

h3 Striped
p.-text Alternate the table row color by applying the modifier class <code>-striped</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_striped.pug

h3 Hover
p.-text Enable a hover state by applying the modifier class <code>-hover</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_hover.pug

.-portal--show
  h3 Portal
  p.-text
    | Enable portal styling by applying class <code>-portal</code>.
    | To display a row in active / selected state, apply class <code>-active</code> to the <code>tr</code>.
  :example(lang="html") include ./_portal.pug

h2 Row States
p.-text
  | Chi offers a wide variety of modifiers to express different row states.

h3 Disabled
p.-text Disable a row by applying the attribute <code>disabled</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_disabled.pug

h3 Success
p.-text Render a success state by applying the modifier class <code>-row--success</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-success.pug

h3 Warning
p.-text Render a warning state by applying the modifier class <code>-row--warning</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-warning.pug

h3 Danger
p.-text Render a danger state by applying the modifier class <code>-row--danger</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-danger.pug

h3 Info
p.-text Render an info state by applying the modifier class <code>-row--info</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-info.pug

h2 Column Sorting
p.-text
  | To express column sorting, apply the class <code>-sorted</code> with one of
  | the following modifiers: <code>-ascending</code> or <code>-descending</code>.

h3 Ascending
:example(lang="html") include ./_sort-ascending.pug

h3 Descending
:example(lang="html") include ./_sort-descending.pug

h2 Content alignment
p.-text
  | Chi also supports additional content alignment with inline text align utilities
  | applying the modifier class <code>-text--left</code> , <code>-text--center</code>
  | or <code>-text--right</code>.

:example(lang="html")
  include ./_common.pug
  table.chi-table
    thead
      tr
        th.-text--left Name
        th.-text--center ID
        th.-text--right Last Login
    tbody
      tr.-md
        td.-text--left Name 1
        td.-text--center name-1
        td.-text--right 2020 3:26 PM
      tr.-md
        td.-text--left Name 2
        td.-text--center name-2
        td.-text--right 2020 3:26 PM
      tr.-md
        td.-text--left Name 3
        td.-text--center name-3
        td.-text--right 2020 3:26 PM

h2 Additional Sizes
p.-text
  | Chi also supports additional table sizes: <code>-xs</code>, <code>-sm</code>, <code>-md</code>,
  |  <code>-lg</code>, <code>-xl</code>.
  | The default size is <code>-md</code>.

h3 Size -xs
p.-text Render a <strong>-xs</strong> size by applying the modifier class <code>-xs</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-xs.pug

h3 Size -sm
p.-text Render a <strong>-sm</strong> size by applying the modifier class <code>-sm</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-sm.pug

h3 Size -md
p.-text Render a <strong>-md</strong> size by applying the modifier class <code>-md</code>.
  |  <strong>-md</strong> is the default size.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-md.pug

h3 Size -lg
p.-text Render a <strong>-lg</strong> size by applying the modifier class <code>-lg</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-lg.pug

h3 Size -xl
p.-text Render a <strong>-xl</strong> size by applying the modifier class <code>-xl</code>.
:example(lang="html") include ./_row-xl.pug

